# --- HTTP Client (outbound network I/O) ---

s" http-get" s" description" s" text" s" Perform an HTTP/HTTPS GET request with extra headers. The headers parameter is a HeapMap of string key-value pairs (use map-new for no extra headers). Returns response body as opaque bytes (HeapByteArray, not string), HTTP status code, and success flag. On failure pushes only flag=false. Domain must be in ETIL_HTTP_ALLOWLIST. Per-session and per-interpret fetch budgets enforced. SSRF protection blocks loopback, RFC1918, link-local, and cloud metadata IPs" meta! drop
s" http-get" s" stack-effect" s" text" s" ( url headers-map -- bytes status-code flag )" meta! drop
s" http-get" s" category" s" text" s" http" meta! drop
s" http-get" s" examples" s" code" s| s" https://httpbin.org/get" map-new http-get -rot 2drop . cr| meta! drop

s" http-post" s" description" s" text" s" Perform an HTTP/HTTPS POST request. The headers parameter is a HeapMap of string key-value pairs. Content-Type is extracted from headers (default: application/octet-stream). The body parameter is a HeapByteArray (use string->bytes to convert a string). Returns response body as opaque bytes (HeapByteArray), HTTP status code, and success flag. On failure pushes only flag=false. Same domain allowlist, fetch budgets, and SSRF protection as http-get" meta! drop
s" http-post" s" stack-effect" s" text" s" ( url headers-map body-bytes -- bytes status-code flag )" meta! drop
s" http-post" s" category" s" text" s" http" meta! drop
s" http-post" s" examples" s" code" s| s" https://httpbin.org/post" map-new s" hello" string->bytes http-post -rot 2drop . cr| meta! drop

# --- MongoDB ---

s" mongo-find" s" description" s" text" s" Query a MongoDB collection. Filter and options accept String, Json, or Map. Options supports: skip, limit, sort, projection, hint, collation, max_time_ms, batch_size. Returns matching documents as a Json value and a success flag. Requires mongo_access permission. Results are tainted (external data)" meta! drop
s" mongo-find" s" stack-effect" s" text" s" ( coll filter opts -- json flag )" meta! drop
s" mongo-find" s" category" s" text" s" mongodb" meta! drop
s" mongo-find" s" examples" s" code" s| s" test" s" {}" s" {}" mongo-find| meta! drop

s" mongo-count" s" description" s" text" s" Count documents in a MongoDB collection. Filter and options accept String, Json, or Map. Uses server-side count_documents() (O(index) not O(N)). Options supports: skip, limit, hint, collation, max_time_ms. Returns the count as an integer and a success flag. Requires mongo_access permission" meta! drop
s" mongo-count" s" stack-effect" s" text" s" ( coll filter opts -- count flag )" meta! drop
s" mongo-count" s" category" s" text" s" mongodb" meta! drop
s" mongo-count" s" examples" s" code" s| s" test" s" {}" s" {}" mongo-count| meta! drop

s" mongo-insert" s" description" s" text" s" Insert a document into a MongoDB collection. Document accepts String, Json, or Map. Returns the inserted document _id as a string and a success flag. Requires mongo_access permission" meta! drop
s" mongo-insert" s" stack-effect" s" text" s" ( coll doc -- inserted-id flag )" meta! drop
s" mongo-insert" s" category" s" text" s" mongodb" meta! drop
s" mongo-insert" s" examples" s" code" s| s" mycoll" s" {}" mongo-insert| meta! drop

s" mongo-update" s" description" s" text" s" Update documents in a MongoDB collection. Filter, update, and options accept String, Json, or Map. The update should use MongoDB update operators ($set, $inc, etc.). Options supports: upsert, hint, collation. Returns the count of modified documents and a success flag. Requires mongo_access permission" meta! drop
s" mongo-update" s" stack-effect" s" text" s" ( coll filter update opts -- count flag )" meta! drop
s" mongo-update" s" category" s" text" s" mongodb" meta! drop
s" mongo-update" s" examples" s" code" s| s" mycoll" s" {}" s" {}" s" {}" mongo-update| meta! drop

s" mongo-delete" s" description" s" text" s" Delete documents from a MongoDB collection. Filter and options accept String, Json, or Map. Options supports: hint, collation. Returns the count of deleted documents and a success flag. Requires mongo_access permission" meta! drop
s" mongo-delete" s" stack-effect" s" text" s" ( coll filter opts -- count flag )" meta! drop
s" mongo-delete" s" category" s" text" s" mongodb" meta! drop
s" mongo-delete" s" examples" s" code" s| s" mycoll" s" {}" s" {}" mongo-delete| meta! drop

